# ZoomAlboom

Read first:
- `docs/product/vision.md`
- `docs/architecture/overview.md`
- `docs/architecture/data-model.md`
- `docs/architecture/rendering.md`
- `docs/architecture/navigation.md`
- `docs/architecture/conventions.md`
- `memory/MEMORY.md`

## Critical rules

- Do not invent a second architecture when docs already define one.
- Keep **canvas/navigation state** separate from **IDE overlay / panel state**.
- Keep domain models independent from Compose UI.
- Use the shared camera transform approach described in `docs/architecture/rendering.md`.
- Put stable architecture in `docs/architecture/*`.
- Put discovered implementation notes and quirks in `memory/MEMORY.md`.

## Dependency direction

`feature -> domain <- data`, with `core` shared.

## Implementation style

- Prefer immutable UI state.
- Avoid putting heavy canvas work on the main thread.
- When adding a new major concept, update docs if the architecture changes.
